config BR2_PACKAGE_TAILSCALE_REEFY
	bool "tailscale-reefy"
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_GO_TARGET_ARCH_SUPPORTS
	depends on !BR2_PACKAGE_TAILSCALE
	select BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_GO
	help
	  Local fork of upstream's tailscale package, carrying two
	  changes that haven't been upstreamed:

	  1. Omits the broken TAILSCALE_INSTALL_SYMLINK hook. Upstream
	     creates /usr/sbin/tailscaled as a symlink to ../bin/tailscaled.
	     With BR2_ROOTFS_MERGED_USR=y (required by systemd),
	     /usr/sbin -> /usr/bin, so the ln -f follows the symlink and
	     overwrites the real binary at /usr/bin/tailscaled with a
	     circular symlink, destroying tailscaled.

	  2. Pins a newer tailscale version than upstream buildroot.

	  Delete this package and switch back to BR2_PACKAGE_TAILSCALE
	  once upstream catches up.

	  https://github.com/tailscale/tailscale
